\if{html}{\figure{logo.png}{options: style='float: right' alt='logo' width='120'}}

Provides automated, reproducible quality control for phenotypic data from plant breeding field trials. Includes trial structure validation (duplicate plots, missing entries, replication balance), statistical and spatial outlier detection, spatial trend diagnostics, missing data analysis with spatial imputation, and automated HTML QC report generation. All functions are pipe-friendly and non-interactive, designed for scripting and batch processing. Integrates seamlessly with 'brapiR2' for end-to-end breeding data pipelines.
